From 34d8e37604b0ddf9da3c0366276fe4eee44398d1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 10:42:58 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 018/174] PGCL: fix arm64, s390, powerpc, sparc
 cross-compilation with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

arm64:
- pgtable-hwdef.h: PTDESC_TABLE_SHIFT, ARM64_HW_PGTABLE_LEVELS, PTE_ADDR_LOW,
  CONT_PTE_SHIFT/SIZE all use MMUPAGE_SHIFT (page table pages are hardware-
  page-sized, not kernel-page-sized)
- pgtable.h: pte_advance_pfn uses MMUPAGE_SHIFT for sub-page stride; set_ptes,
  clear_full_ptes, wrprotect_ptes, clear_young_dirty_ptes, contpte_try_fold,
  pte_leaf_size, folded page table alignment all MMUPAGE-aware
- kernel-pgtable.h: SWAPPER_BLOCK_SHIFT, INIT_DIR_SIZE, INIT_IDMAP_DIR_SIZE,
  INIT_IDMAP_FDT_SIZE use MMUPAGE_SIZE for page table page sizing
- memory.h: THREAD_SHIFT, NVHE_STACK_SHIFT use MMUPAGE_SHIFT
- vmlinux.lds.S: page directory spacing uses MMUPAGE_SIZE
- pi/map_range.c: early identity mapping uses MMUPAGE_SHIFT/SIZE/MASK
- kvm/mmu.c: stage-2 page fault vma_shift uses MMUPAGE_SHIFT; guard
  CONT_PTE_SHIFT case when it equals MMUPAGE_SHIFT to avoid duplicate case

s390:
- thread_info.h: THREAD_SIZE and BOOT_STACK_SIZE use MMUPAGE_SIZE
- relocate_kernel.S: lghi→lgfi for PAGE_SIZE (exceeds 16-bit signed imm);
  nill mask generalized to (PAGE_MASK & 0xffff)
- sclp.h: EARLY_SCCB_SIZE, EXT_SCCB_READ_SCP/CPU use MMUPAGE_SIZE (hardware
  SCCB buffers are 4KB-page-aligned)
- sclp drivers: SCCB allocation sizes use MMUPAGE_SIZE

powerpc:
- Kconfig: relax ARCH_FORCE_MAX_ORDER range from 12..12 to 8..12 for PPC64
  with 4K pages (MAX_ORDER + PAGE_SHIFT must not exceed SECTION_SIZE_BITS)
- vmlinux.lds.S: DATA_SHIFT check uses MMUPAGE_SIZE instead of PAGE_SIZE

sparc:
- pgtable_64.h: PMD_SHIFT, PMD_BITS, PUD_BITS, PGDIR_BITS, PTRS_PER_PTE all
  use MMUPAGE_SHIFT (page table pages are hardware-page-sized)
- page_64.h: DCACHE_ALIASING_POSSIBLE checks MMUPAGE_SHIFT
- tsb.h: all page table walk macros use MMUPAGE_SHIFT for index computation
- copy_page.S: PAGE_SIZE_REM computed from PAGE_SIZE modulo, not PAGE_SHIFT
- ultra.S: dcache flush check uses MMUPAGE_SHIFT

Cross-compile results with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4: 11/11 architectures PASS
(x86_64, arm64, riscv64, arm32, powerpc64, s390x, mips, sparc64, alpha,
m68k, loongarch).

x86_64 boot test: PASS (SMP=4, all fork/COW/clustering tests pass).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
